0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 15 "x-int: x=2, x=4" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 42 
"d2 positive: (-infinity, 2), (4, infinity)" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 19 "d2 negative: (2, 4)" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 12 "y-int: y=12
8" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 19 "up large end limits" }}}{PARA 0 "" 
0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 841 "3.  Polynomials:  L
ocal extreme values and monotonicity.  Beyond information of the type \+
gathered above about intercepts and signs of a polynomial,  other impo
rtant information can be determined from the so called \"critical poin
ts\" of a polynomial.  The critical points of a polynomial are the int
ercepts of its derivative.  Since the derivative of a function at a po
int represents the slope of the tangent line to the graph of the that \+
function at the point, then the intercepts of the derivative are place
s where the the tangent lines to the function are flat, i.e., are hori
zontal lines.  At such places the graph is neither increasing nor decr
easing.  Elsewhere the graph must be either increasing or decreasing. \+
 For a polynomial, local extreme values (local maximums or local minim
ums) must occur at the intercepts of the derivative.  " }}{PARA 0 "" 
0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 80 "     The follwing fe
atures are important in analyzing the graph of a polynomial:" }}{PARA 
0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 41 "     f.   criti
cal points of the function" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 99 "           \+
           For a polynomial these are the intercepts of the derivative
 of the polynomial" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 67 "     g.    local ma
ximum points of the graph of a function y = f(x)" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 274 "                      These are points (x,y) on the grap
h of the function for which the y-value is locally the largest value o
f the function.  Nearby values on the graph are lower.  For a polynomi
als the x-value of the point (x,y) must be a critical point of the pol
ynomial." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 67 "     h.   local minimum point
s of the graph of a function y = f(x) " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
276 "                      These are points (x,y) on the graph of the \+
function for which the y-value is locally the smallest value of the fu
nction.  Nearby values on the graph are higher.  For a polynomials the
 x-value of the point (x,y) must be a critical point of the polynomial
." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 108 "     i.    regions (intervals) in t
he domain of the function where the values of the function are increas
ing" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 249 "                       Those regi
ons where the graph rises as the graph is traversed from left to right
.  For a continuous function, and in particular for polynomials, these
 regions are bounded by the critical points and may stretch to +/- inf
inity." }}{PARA 257 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 108 "     j.    regions (interval
s) in the domain of the function where the values of the function are \+
decreasing" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 249 "                       Tho
se regions where the graph falls as the graph is traversed from left t
o right.  For a continuous function, and in particular for polynomials
, these regions are bounded by the critical points and may stretch to \+
+/- infinity." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 275 "For each of the following polynomials,  provide a graph \+
of the polynomial.  Choose a range that will optimally represent the f
eatures of the graph.  Include the graph of the deriviative of the pol
ynomial on the plot.   Plot the function in red and the derviative in \+
green.   " }{TEXT 269 4 "Also" }{TEXT -1 89 ", for each polynomial fin
d each of the above ten graphcial characteristics (a.  thru j.):" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "a.  " }
{XPPEDIT 18 0 "y = x^2-2*x-15;" "6#/%\"yG,(*$%\"xG\"\"#\"\"\"*&F(F)F'F
)!\"\"\"#:F+" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 4 "b.  " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "y = x^3-6*x^2+9*x+6;" "6#/%\"yG,**$%\"xG\"
\"$\"\"\"*&\"\"'F)*$F'\"\"#F)!\"\"*&\"\"*F)F'F)F)F+F)" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 
"" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "c.  " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "y
 = -3*x^4+4*x^3+30*x^2+36*x+6;" "6#/%\"yG,,*&\"\"$\"\"\"*$%\"xG\"\"%F(
!\"\"*&F+F(*$F*F'F(F(*&\"#IF(*$F*\"\"#F(F(*&\"#OF(F*F(F(\"\"'F(" }}
{PARA 257 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 
0 32 "a3:=x^2-2*x-15;\na33:=diff(a3,x);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 
20 "6#>%#a3G,(*$)%\"xG\"\"#\"\"\"F**&F)F*F(F*!\"\"\"#:F," }}{PARA 11 "
" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%$a33G,&%\"xG\"\"#F'!\"\"" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 ">
 " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 25 "plot([a3,a33],x=-10..10);" }}{PARA 13 "" 1 "
